President Barack Obama has updated the Presidential Delegation to the Closing Ceremony of the 2014 Olympic Winter Games in Sochi, Russia. The delegation will attend athletic events, meet with U.S. athletes, and attend the Closing Ceremony. The delegation will be led by Deputy Secretary of State William J. Burns and will also include United States Ambassador to the Russian Federation Michael A. McFaul, Billie Jean King (Member of the President's Council on Fitness, Sports and Nutrition and International Tennis Hall of Fame), Bonnie Blair (five-time Olympic gold medalist in speed skating), and Dr. Eric Heiden (five-time Olympic gold medalist in speed skating).